Git and GitHub have become essential tools for modern software development.

Almost every software company uses Git for version control and GitHub (or similar platforms) for collaboration.

Learning Git and GitHub helps you:

- Build real-world development skills.
- Collaborate with teams efficiently.
- Contribute to open-source projects.
