## Key Terms

### Repository (Repo)

A repository is a storage location for your project. It contains your project files along with the complete history of changes.

---

### Version

A version is a saved state of your project at a specific point in time.

---

### Commit

A commit is a snapshot of your project. Every commit records the changes made since the previous commit along with a message describing those changes.

---

### Branch

A branch is an independent line of development. It allows you to work on new features or fixes without affecting the main project.

---

### Clone

Cloning means creating a complete copy of a remote repository on your local computer.

---

### Push

Push uploads your local commits to a remote repository such as GitHub.

---

### Pull

Pull downloads the latest changes from a remote repository and updates your local repository.

